42 “SECTION 2. ORS 678.733 is amended to read:
43 “678.733. (1) The Health Licensing Office may issue a residential care facility administrator li-
44 cense to an applicant who:
45 “(a) Is at least 21 years of age;
HA to HB 4040 Page 2

1 “(b) Has earned at least a high school diploma or its equivalent, as indicated by evidence of the
2 following, in a form deemed sufficient by the office:
3 “(A) Completion of high school or an equivalent educational level;
4 “(B) Passage of an approved high school equivalency test, including but not limited to the Gen-
5 eral Educational Development (GED) test; or
6 “(C) Graduation from a post-secondary institution;
7 “(c)(A) For at least two of the last five years has been employed in a professional or managerial
8 capacity in a health or social service related field, or has a combination of experience and education
9 deemed sufficient by the office; or
10 “(B) Has earned at least a bachelor’s degree [in a health or social service related field];
11 “(d) Has completed at least 40 hours of training approved by the office by rule;
12 “(e) Pays a licensure fee; and
13 “(f) Passes an examination described in ORS 678.743.
14 “(2) Evidence of the education described in subsection (1)(b) of this section may be provided by
15 a diploma or other document, or by facts, circumstances or other indicators deemed sufficient by the
16 office.
17 “(3) When issuing a license under this section, the office shall consider the qualifications for
18 employment under ORS 443.004.
19 “SECTION 3. The amendments to ORS 678.733 by section 2 of this 2026 Act apply to ap-
20 plications for licensure under ORS 678.733 submitted to the Health Licensing Office on or
21 after the operative date specified in section 4 of this 2026 Act.
22 “SECTION 4. (1) The amendments to ORS 678.733 by section 2 of this 2026 Act become
23 operative on January 1, 2027.
24 “(2) The Health Licensing Office make take any action before the operative date specified
25 in subsection (1) of this section that is necessary to enable the office to exercise, on and
26 after the operative date specified in subsection (1) of this section, all of the duties, functions
27 and powers conferred on the office by the amendments to ORS 678.733 by section 2 of this
28 2026 Act.
