32 “SECTION 5. ORS 411.447 is amended to read:
33 “411.447. (1) As used in this section, ‘correctional facility’ means:
34 “(a) A local correctional facility as defined in ORS 169.005;
35 “(b) A Department of Corrections institution as defined in ORS 421.005; or
36 “(c) A youth correction facility as defined in ORS 162.135.
37 “(2) The Department of Human Services or the Oregon Health Authority shall:
38 “(a) Suspend, instead of terminate, the medical assistance of a person who is residing in a
39 correctional facility; or
40 “(b) Enroll the person in the appropriate benefits package based on the person’s eligibility
41 for prerelease benefits, as authorized by federal law.
42 “(3) Upon notification that a person described in subsection (2) of this section is not residing in
43 a correctional facility or that the person is admitted to a medical institution outside of the
44 correctional facility for a period of hospitalization, the department or the authority shall reinstate
45 the [person’s medical assistance if the person is eligible for medical assistance] medical assistance
HA to HB 4040 Page 3

1 benefits for which the person is eligible at the time of release or hospitalization.
2 “(4)(a) A designee of a correctional facility may apply for medical assistance on behalf of a
3 person, while the person is residing in the correctional facility, for the purpose of establishing el-
4 igibility for medical assistance prior to release, with full benefits upon the person’s release from
5 the correctional facility or during a period of hospitalization that will occur outside of the
6 correctional facility.
7 “(b) The designee may obtain information necessary to determine eligibility for medical assist-
8 ance, including the person’s Social Security number or information that is not otherwise subject to
9 disclosure under ORS 411.320 or 413.175. The information obtained under this paragraph may be
10 used only for the purpose of assisting the person in applying for medical assistance and may not be
11 redisclosed without the person’s authorization.
12 “[(c) If the person is determined eligible for medical assistance, the effective date of the person’s
13 medical assistance shall be the date the person is released from the correctional facility or the date the
14 person begins the period of hospitalization outside of the correctional facility.]
15 “(5) This section does not extend eligibility to an otherwise ineligible person or extend medical
16 assistance to a person if matching federal funds are not available to pay for the medical assistance.
