40 any vendor that provides research and analysis to the commission; and
41 “[(b)] (B) Inviting public comment on any research or analysis tool or health economic measures
42 to be relied upon by the commission in the commission’s decision-making.
43 “[(3)(a)] (4)(a) The commission shall develop and maintain a list of health services ranked by
44 priority, from the most important to the least important, representing the comparative benefits of
45 each service to the population to be served.
