7 “SECTION 12. ORS 679.025 is amended to read:
8 “679.025. (1) A person may not practice dentistry or purport to be a dentist without a valid li-
9 cense to practice dentistry issued by the Oregon Board of Dentistry.
10 “(2) Subsection (1) of this section does not apply to:
11 “(a) Dentists licensed in another state or country making a clinical presentation sponsored by
12 a bona fide dental society or association or an accredited dental educational institution approved
13 by the board.
14 “(b) Bona fide full-time students of dentistry who, during the period of their enrollment and as
15 a part of the course of study in an Oregon accredited dental education program, engage in clinical
16 studies on the premises of such institution or in a clinical setting located off the premises of the
17 institution if the facility, the instructional staff and the course of study to be pursued at the off-
18 premises location meet minimum requirements prescribed by the rules of the board and the clinical
19 study is performed under the indirect supervision of a member of the faculty.
20 “(c) Bona fide full-time students of dentistry who, during the period of their enrollment and as
21 a part of the course of study in a dental education program located outside of Oregon that is ac-
22 credited by the Commission on Dental Accreditation of the American Dental Association or its
23 successor [agency] organization, engage in community-based or clinical studies as an elective or
24 required rotation in a clinical setting located in Oregon if the community-based or clinical studies
25 meet minimum requirements prescribed by the rules of the board and are performed under the indi-
26 rect supervision of a [member of the faculty of the Oregon Health and Science University School of
27 Dentistry] faculty member of a dental education program accredited by the Commission on
28 Dental Accreditation of the American Dental Association, or its successor organization.
29 “(d) Candidates who are preparing for a licensure examination to practice dentistry and whose
30 application has been accepted by the board or its agent, if the clinical preparation is conducted in
31 a clinic located on premises approved for that purpose by the board and if the procedures are lim-
32 ited to examination only. This exception shall exist for a period not to exceed two weeks imme-
33 diately prior to a regularly scheduled licensure examination.
34 “(e) Dentists practicing in the discharge of official duties as employees of the United States
35 Government and any of its agencies.
36 “(f) Instructors of dentistry, whether full- or part-time, while exclusively engaged in teaching
37 activities and while employed in accredited dental educational institutions.
38 “(g) Dentists who are employed by public health agencies and who are not engaged in the direct
39 delivery of clinical dental services to patients.
40 “(h) Persons licensed to practice medicine in the State of Oregon in the regular discharge of
41 their duties.
42 “(i) Persons qualified to perform services relating to general anesthesia or sedation under the
43 direct supervision of a licensed dentist.
44 “(j)(A) Dentists licensed in another country and in good standing, while practicing dentistry
45 without compensation for no more than five consecutive days in any 12-month period, provided the
HA to HB 4040 Page 10

1 dentist submits an application to the board at least 10 days before practicing dentistry under this
2 subparagraph and the application is approved by the board.
3 “(B) Dentists licensed in another state or United States territory and practicing in this state
4 under ORS 676.347.
5 “(k) Persons practicing dentistry upon themselves as the patient.
6 “(L) Dental hygienists, dental assistants or dental technicians performing services under the
7 supervision of a licensed dentist in accordance with the rules adopted by the board.
8 “(m) A person licensed as a denturist under ORS 680.500 to 680.565 engaged in the practice of
9 denture technology.
10 “(n) An expanded practice dental hygienist who renders services authorized by a permit issued
11 by the board pursuant to ORS 680.200.
12 “SECTION 13. (1) The amendments to ORS 679.025 by section 12 of this 2026 Act become
13 operative on January 1, 2027.
