32 condition is medically stationary are not compensable except for the following:
33 “(A) Services provided to a worker who has been determined to be permanently and totally
34 disabled.
35 “(B) Prescription medications.
36 “(C) Services necessary to administer prescription medication or monitor the administration of
37 prescription medication.
38 “(D) Prosthetic devices, braces and supports.
39 “(E) Services necessary to monitor the status, replacement or repair of prosthetic devices,
40 braces and supports.
41 “(F) Services provided pursuant to an accepted claim for aggravation under ORS 656.273.
42 “(G) Services provided pursuant to an order issued under ORS 656.278.
43 “(H) Services that are necessary to diagnose the worker’s condition.
44 “(I) Life-preserving modalities similar to insulin therapy, dialysis and transfusions.
45 “(J) With the approval of the insurer or self-insured employer, palliative care that the worker’s
