16 quarter, such base year shall be extended a calendar quarter. Except as provided in subsection (2)
17 of this section, no such extension of an individual’s base year shall exceed four calendar quarters.
18 “(2) If the director finds that during and prior to the individual’s base year the individual has
19 had a period of temporary total disability caused by illness or injury and has received compensation
20 under ORS chapter 656 for a period of temporary total disability during the greater part of any
21 calendar quarter, the individual’s base year shall be extended as many calendar quarters as neces-
22 sary to establish a valid claim, up to a maximum of four calendar quarters prior to the quarter in
23 which the illness or injury occurred, if the individual:
24 “(a) Files a claim for benefits not later than the fourth calendar week of unemployment follow-
25 ing whichever is the latest of the following dates:
26 “(A) The date the individual is released to return to work by the attending physician[, as defined
27 in ORS chapter 656, or a nurse practitioner authorized to provide compensable medical services under
28 ORS 656.245] as defined in ORS 656.005 (12); or
29 “(B) The date of mailing of a notice of claim closure pursuant to ORS chapter 656; and
30 “(b) Files such a claim within the three-year period immediately following the commencement
31 of such period of illness or injury.
32 “(3) Notwithstanding the provisions of this section, benefits payable as a result of the use of
33 wages paid in a calendar quarter prior to the individual’s current base year shall not exceed one-
34 third of such wages less benefits paid previously as a result of the use of such wages in computing
35 a previous benefit determination.
36
37 “CAPTIONS
38
39 “SECTION 60. The unit captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for the conven-
40 ience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or express any
41 legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
42
43 “EFFECTIVE DATE
44
45 “SECTION 61. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
HA to HB 4040 Page 69

1 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
2 on its passage.”.
